// sink.su — counts inbound axons, emits a stat-counter axon.
//
// Companion to echo.su. Receives axons on R_output (so it can absorb
// what echo emits) and emits a count-update on R_stat.
//
// In v0.0 this file is the seed source; the running service is the
// Python stub `kernel.services.SinkService`. See echo.su for the
// service-shape convention this file commits to.

// State carried across ticks. In Sutra this would be threaded
// through a tail-recursive loop; the v0.1 loader needs to map
// kernel ticks onto either single-step invocations of on_axon (the
// current convention) or the loop-as-RNN pattern Sutra uses
// natively. Documented as an open question for the loader.

function vector on_axon(vector input_axon) {
    // Sink does no transformation on the input — it would, in a real
    // service, increment a counter that lives in the per-process
    // state vector and emit it. The v0.0 shim does the counting on
    // the Python side; this .su file documents the shape, not the
    // counting logic.
    return input_axon;
}
